column5: Made it out on friday for a last go at some crappie fishing on the Ottawa river system.What a great day with good company for the afternoon Trent showed up till dark with me!Managed to take home a few for the table and let lots go for another day.The ice is still very thick but caution is to be had made to shore.Looking forward to some open water fishing soon
Some beauty crappie there Mr. Twister.  Good stuff.  When's dinner  Joey

Way to go.  ...they are such tasty and scrappy little fish,i love getting about a dozen for an awsome fish-fry...thanks for the report,as i see there is still lots of ice where you are,well with the forecasted temps for the next few days it wont be around very much longer....cheers
My mouth is watering. Nice work!!
They do look good, they are fun to catch in the spring, never caught one through the ice.  Enjoy....  Maureen
